const PI = 3.14;
PI = 42;  /// this will throw an error

    What is the difference between var and let?
    var has a global scope while let has a block scope, var can be redeclared, while let can not.
    
    What is the difference between var and const?
    var is global scope while const is a block scope, var can be redeclared or reassigned, while const can only be mutated and nor 
    redeclared or reassigned.
    
    What is the difference between let and const?
    let can be reassigned, const cannot be.
    
    What is hoisting?
    the ability of the code to know that there has been a termed declared but it hasent reached that part in the code yet 
    so it is undefined. var has the ability to do that because it has a global scope but the others do not so it only works for var

